\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sb120\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Ps::0>[ In this scene, we will add a little mystery. Initially, the reader might think that there is something romantic between Laura and Evan. We are going to let them think that although that is not true. In this scene, is where Laura and Evan begin to discuss the real reasons why Maggie is quitting school. This is where the seed for Evan's internship program idea gets planted. Although we don't find that out in the scene.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 I'm going to include a lot of narrative from the rough draft scene. However, feel free to replace that with more compelling narrative of your own.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 In the last scene, we left off with Evan feeling a bit of panic over Maggie's decision to leave school.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 Maggie, feeling sad, asked Evan to spend the night and so he did. This scene picks up in the morning following the day when Maggie revealed her plans to quit school to Evan.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 We want to start the scene informing the readers that Evan sucked over at Maggie's request. However, we quickly want to get into Evan's mind. Inform the readers that Evan was awake all night feeling uneasy about Maggie's decision. While he was still at a heightened state of panic, part of them was beginning to wonder if there was something more to the story.}
\par\plain \f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 At some point in the scene, Let the reader know that Evan needed to know, had to know what was going on. But let's not give away the mystery. The mystery comes when Evan whisper something in Laura's ear when Maggie's not looking. We don't immediately reveal what this is, so the reader may think they're having an affair. However, Evan needs to know why Maggie's quitting school, and is convinced that Laura knows her reason and will tell him.}
\par\plain \f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 ]}
