\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0 Evan had stayed overnight. They just finished eating breakfast and were minutes away from leaving together. Maggie had to get to school, and Evan would be heading home.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 Laura had just emerged from her bedroom and was preparing a bowl of cereal for herself. Evan needed to say something to Laura, but he couldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t find an opportunity with Maggie nearby.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 Looking for an excuse to get close to Laura, Evan grabbed a small glass and poured milk from the carton she used for her cereal. He took his time, hoping Maggie would look away for a split-second. When she did, Evan whispered something in Laura\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s ear.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 Laura looked back over her shoulder to make sure Maggie wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t focused on them, and then she nodded yes to Evan. Maggie caught only part of this quiet exchange between Laura and Evan. }
\par\plain \f0\fs26\b0
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Mostly joking, but she wondered):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf6 <$Scr_Cs::4>\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Why are you guys acting so secretive? Do I have to worry about you two?\u8221\'94<!$Scr_Cs::4>}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Laura<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(quick with a lie):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf6 <$Scr_Cs::4>\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93\u8220\'93We\u8217\'92re just talking about your Christmas present.\u8221\'94<!$Scr_Cs::4>}
