\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sb120\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs28\b0\i0 Evan rinsed his glass of milk out in the sink and asked Maggie if she was ready to leave. Maggie said she was, and they walked together toward the door. With Maggie\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s back to them, Laura and Evan exchanged a glance that served as a confirmation of their plan.<!$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs28\b0\i0 Evan walked Maggie to her car and kissed her before going to his. To avoid suspicion, Evan pulled out of his parking spot at the same time as Maggie. They pulled out of the parking lot one after the other. Maggie headed south toward school, and Evan headed north toward the highway.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\i0 Evan turned left into the parking lot of a convenience store. He waited there for a few minutes until he was comfortable the coast was clear. Then he got back on the road and headed back to Maggie and Laura\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s apartment.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\i0 Evan knocked on the door, and Laura answered. }
